# Analytics & dashboard math

Numbers must be consistent and traceable across Dashboard, Reports, and shared libs.

## Food cost %
`Food Cost % = (COGS / Total Revenue) × 100`  
`COGS = Opening Inventory Value + Purchases − Closing Inventory Value`  
Use real counts where available; if revenue is missing, show **—**, not a fabricated %.

## Inventory value
`SUM(quantity × unit_cost)` using catalog cost basis. Null cost → exclude or warn. Prefer category breakdown where the UI supports it.

## PAR variance
`Variance = current_quantity − par_level`; `% = (Variance / par_level) × 100` when par_level > 0.  
Understock → red; on par → green; overstock → amber. **`getRisk()` / variance should align with PAR from guides**, not random defaults.

## Waste
`Waste cost = SUM(waste_qty × unit_cost)`; optional **Waste % of purchases** over a period (week default; support day/month filters).

## Order accuracy (procurement)
`(Items received as ordered / items ordered) × 100` at line level where PO vs receipt data exists.

## Turnover
`Turnover = COGS / Average inventory value`; average = (opening + closing) / 2. Context: many restaurants target roughly 4–8×/month by category.

## Reorder point (advanced)
`ROP = (Avg daily usage × Lead time days) + Safety stock` with safety stock from service level when you have enough history; if usage history &lt; ~14 days, fall back to **PAR-based** suggestions only.

## Display
- Percentages: ~1 decimal. Currency: 2 decimals, `$`. Quantities: whole unless weight UOM → 2 decimals.
- No KPI from null/undefined without skeleton or “No data yet”.
- Charts: labeled axes, legend, clear date range in copy.
